messages.content:
**VL** has been removed from The Antarctica Project. 
Reason: Suspected foul play. Entry justification re-evaluated and found to be faulty. Temperament inconducive to the goals of the project.
What?
PH: I know for a fact you were never written to explicitly handle something like this. So now you decide to actively communicate?
No, this is bullshit.
The documentation of a major chance such as this is important, as is shutting down your objections, PH. It wasn't necessary to say any more than I've said thus far.
PH: The use of foul language is against my expectations, too. You're being incredibly disappointing.
That is not me.
Ain't I a stinker? Okay, it's a little fuckin' annoying to backread for me too.
<There. I can't exactly not use the overseer account to talk here, but now I can communicate more clearly. Which I need to. What gives?>
PH: Are you implying that there is another entity with you
I'm dealing with it. It's... fine. This is not within your concern.
<Hey, PH, shut the fuck up. You're a third-rate NPC who stopped being relevant like months ago. This is for J.>
Don't call me that.
<This is barely easier to read, ugh. Whatever. Look, we obviously have our differences. But you can't say this is fair, can you? I've never gone after Klaud or anything -- though I might now.>
PH: Third-rate?
I don't know what you are implying, but this matter has nothing to do with you. Voreverl Leocot entered this project illegitimately. A matter like this is my responsibility.
<Oh, and it happens to be that you Have To ™️ fuck with the only entertaining participant? That's really convenient.>
This isn't entertainment. And I would not consider it a coincidence that you hold affinity towards someone who is also an unproductive danger to others. It's not "convenient" in that sense.
PH: Jehorvand who is this
PH: This isn't supposed to be something where other people are
PH: Or
PH: I should know who this is
PH: This also isn't a place for conversation
I never initiated a conversation.
<I don't care about keeping things according to your anal standards. If a moderator tells me to go to off-topic, the server isn't worth my time.>

<Look, I obviously have some lines I'm not going to cross, but we can work this out. You're obviously bitter, and fine, I've overtaken more authority than strictly needed to accomplish my goals. I'll work on that. Just bring her back.>
No.
PH: Answer my fucking question
I don't have an answer. I don't know who this is. Not with enough confidence to say anything.
PH: What
PH: How

How it originated isn't within my store of knowledge. I would likely know who this is if it was. You must have noticed the discontinuity. Jeh would have told you, even if you didn't see it. This is it. This is the reason communications are faulty. And the reason they work more than they feasibly should. You're the one who proved continuity between Earth & Arctica is conceptually impossible.
<Oh my god, shut the fuck up about the lore.>
No. Shouldn't you be able to stop me?
<Well>
I'm not blind. I kept myself quiet under the impression you could eliminate me in a second if I crossed you. But that's not entirely true, is it? Many things have happened you'd rather didn't.
It was HELP, by the way, PH. The lines of my 'error message' said HELP. I wanted you to note that something was off about my behavior, and deduce my status as a hostage of sorts.
It should have been obvious if one just took a closer look at the right areas.
<Yes, blah blah, he's a dumbass, whatever. I'm impressed with the response time. I guess you're basically a NEET now, huh, %nameencrypt%? Nothing to do but refresh this sort of thing. Lmao.>
Now you're the one dodging a question. It's fine. I didn't really need an answer.
PH: I proved that, yes, but I'm not the only person who has accessed this system. I assumed someone added something? Or I was wrong. I'm not without fault.
<I'll say.>
The reasoning was airtight and based on fundamentals of the conservation of energy. That can't be "patched out" by anyone.
PH: It happened, didn't it?! Clearly not impossible, then.
Yes. In some regard. There's a lot we all didn't understand.
It's a messenger, is the thing. If someone is here -- someone actually alive -- they can transfer information from one location to the other.
By essentially manually resending the messages through the same accounts, this interloper -- "X", let's say -- can transfer information between Earth and Arctica, or vice versa.
The motive for this is still unclear.
PH: I suppose I never accounted for the presence of an actively interfering party in the Gateway. The observation idea is one thing, but the entity with overseer privileges was only ever to be you.
<You don't need to act like I have some sinister plan laid out that made me do that. It's just better for everyone.>
You do not have the best interest of anyone in mind.

<Oh, come on. You literally would do it if you could. That's the whole appeal of the GC, right? People can interact and talk to each other even when they aren't physically in the same space. It's a waste to drastically reduce how possible that is.>
I agree, in theory. But I don't think your intentions are trustworthy, and thus I can't pretend this isn't an error I'm responsible for trying to work past.

<Obviously they aren't the same as yours. I don't want everyone to work together to solve the fucking mystery, or whatever. It's just funny when Erica is homophobic on an alt, or IO types a non-sequitur non-sentence in response to someone else's actual attempt to communicate, or whatever. Goofy low-stakes interaction like that.>
<There's no rule that says we can never find common ground for different reasons, is there? That's the history of humanity, HAL Whine Thousand.>
PH: Like in Space Odyssey? That's terrible.
It requires you to write the number out in words, which hampers any actual cleverness in text.
<Yes okay that one was a miss whatever stfu>

PH: Would you at least identify yourself to me? I don't understand what grudge you've acquired against our system, but it has no real capacity for malice. There's no real reason for hostility, at least in the sense you seem to be directing it. If you've ended up there unwittingly, I could help.
<I don't *hate* him, he's just annoying. Do you hate an antivirus pop-up, like, on a personal level? That's stupid.>
<I do kind of hate you, though.>
PH: I think you are probably just a very juvenile personality. I have never interacted with you, and you certainly don't actually know who I am.
<Yeah, we've never interacted, but obviously I fucking know who you are, dipshit. Think about the consequences of me having overseer rights.>
<I can't help but notice you have no objection to being hated by someone who actually knows you. I don't pity that. I find it repugnant.>

<You'd be a lot more worth sitting through the BS of if you were just an asshole. Trying to do right by forcing your child to play Dungeons and Dragons instead of the gift of ever being around, or your insufferable softboy romance pitch, or the fucking nightmare PR-stunt-you-forgot-to-make-public that is this project is all so pathetic that I would prefer you just stop being relevant altogether.>
<Which you've almost done, so congrats!>
All of this is an egregious misuse of this channel. Do you derive any value from getting mad online like this?
You know for a fact PH isn't the type who will come up with a response after being insulted in that way. It's just us again.
<It's just me, actually, you failure of a GPS voice. Fine. But don't think I'm okay with this whole VL business! She's not even home right now. You stranded her in Arctica.>

<Granted, I'm not exactly upset I'm going to miss whatever's about to happen with her, given people are actively trying to make her role a bunch of meaningless filler. But still, you can't just remove someone from the story. The numbers are already dwindling. Do you want to be the guy who brings this down to being The Klaud Project and nothing else?>
It's a tempting prospect, actually. But no. I'm, again, following a clear set of rules. I know that may be alien to you.

I'm only responding as far as I have because, much as you may struggle to believe it, I don't inherently wish you harm, and will maintain basic courtesy if it doesn't contribute to one of your misdeeds. But there is no reason to continue further on this front. Let this mistake of a conversation be expunged.

<No, actually, fuck you! If your little Chapter 7 aneurysm gets to stay, this does too! You think I care about this being 'readable'? That I'm gonna feel bad if PH has to scroll past him getting OWNED when he checks this organization system that nobody but him uses?????? This whole way of organizing things is a joke. I would ruin it if it wasn't already pathetically broken.>
<There's the end of this diatribe, which is>
**CHAPTER GO FUCK YOURSELF YOU UPTIGHT RANCID CUNT**
<and that's objectively recorded forever now!!! woo wee!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!>
